// LANDING VARIANT C — Accessibility and readability
// Targets WCAG AA throughout: ≥4.5:1 contrast for text, ≥3:1 for UI.
// Tradeoff: more space per element, fewer items visible above the fold.
//
// Key patterns:
// - Body text ≥16px, headings use a clear descending scale (48→36→24→16)
// - Line-height 1.7 on all body copy — readable on small screens
// - All interactive elements ≥44px tall (touch target minimum)
// - Status badges: icon + text + color (never color alone)
// - Problem cards use icon + title + desc (no decorative emojis as sole indicator)
// - ROI calculator: sliders have visible labels + focus rings
// - Plan cards: "Más popular" communicated with text badge + border, not color alone
// - FAQ: focus-visible outline on accordion buttons
// - Contrast: dark text on light bg, not opacity-based muting

